3 (2) When an employer operates two or more premises in the conduct of business they
4 shall be considered one premises for the purposes of this chapter if the labor dispute at one
5 makes it impossible or impractical to conduct work at the others or in a normal manner.
6 (3) This section does not apply if it is shown to the satisfaction of the director that the
7 individual:
8 (a) Is unemployed due to a lockout, as defined in ORS 662.205, at the factory, establish-
9 ment or other premises at which the individual was last employed; or
10 (b)(A) Is not participating in or financing or directly interested in the labor dispute that
11 caused the unemployment of the individual; and
12 (B) Does not belong to a grade or class of workers of which, immediately before the
13 commencement of the labor dispute, there were members employed at the premises at which
14 the labor dispute occurs, any of whom are participating in or financing or directly interested
15 in the dispute.
16 (4) An individual who meets all other applicable benefit eligibility requirements of this
17 chapter is not disqualified from receipt of benefits by this section if:
18 (a) The individual was laid off from the employer prior to commencement of the labor
19 dispute, did not work for the employer more than seven days during the 21 calendar days
20 immediately prior to the commencement of the labor dispute and meets the requirements
21 of subsection (3)(b)(A) of this section; or
22 (b) During the labor dispute, the individual’s job or position is filled by the employer
23 hiring a permanent replacement and the following conditions are met:
24 (A) The individual subsequently unilaterally abandons the labor dispute and affirmatively
25 seeks reemployment with the employer; and
26 (B) The individual meets the requirements of subsection (3)(b)(A) of this section.
27 (5) An individual who maintains membership in a labor union or who continues to pay
28 labor union dues does not violate the provisions of subsection (3)(b)(A) of this section for the
29 purposes of subsection (4) of this section.
