36 glutaraldehyde, nitrite concentrations above physiological levels, hypochlorite or soap.
37 (b) “Bias crime” means:
38 (A) Conduct that, in the determination of the director, more likely than not constitutes a bias
39 crime in the first degree described in ORS 166.165 or a bias crime in the second degree described
40 in ORS 166.155; or
41 (B) Similar conduct, as defined by the director by rule.
42 (c) “Drug” means a controlled substance as defined in ORS 475.005.
43 (d) “Last chance agreement” means a reasonable agreement:
44 (A) Between an employer and an employee who has violated the employer’s reasonable written
45 policy, has engaged in drug, cannabis or alcohol use connected with work or has admitted to alcohol
